acy for those living on the fringes of society will create a more vibrant and robust democracy for all. He is the winner of the 2021 Brown Democracy Medal for his continuing work to restore voting rights and connect Americans along shared social values.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aPublic Policy. 4aU.S. History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civil Rights.2bisacsh  avoting rights, voting rights in florida, felons and the right to vote, felon voting rights.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501763762zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501763762zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501763762/original  a978-3-11-073908-4 Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA